TAPE4-RECORD 1.1

	TIT

	1-80

	A80

		TIT:	80 characters of user indetification

REPEAT TAPE4-RECORD 1.1 for a total of three times


TAPE4-RECORD 1.2

	IVIB,	MOLNEQ

           5,       10

          I5	    I5

		IVIB:	(0,1) selects input for vibrational data:
                          
                           = 0 (kinetic temepratures (K) )
			
			   = 1 (population)

		MOLNEQ:  place holder for future input 

 ******  these records applicable only if IVIB eq 1 ***

TAPE4-RECORD 2.1 

 	CHRD(1)

              3

	 2x, A1

		CHRD(1):	a flag which indicates the beginning of input for
			        a new molecule; must be set to '-'


	The next two records are required for the following five molecules:
         H2O, CO2, O3, C0 and NO, in that order. All molecules must be input,
	 even if not used in NLTE calculations.
  
          
TAPE4-RECORD 2.2 

	HMNLTE

	    10

	   A10

		HMNLTE: 	molecule name

TAPE4-RECORD 2.3

	ALT,   (TEM(I),I=1,NUM)

           (F7.0,7F11.3/(18X,6F11.3))

		ALT:	altitude (km)

		TEM(I):	Temperature difference from ground state (K) for each mode I. Set to zero if the mode
			is not desired. See Table IV for allowed modes and input order. 

REPEAT TAPE4-RECORD 2.3 for all altitudes; the altitude range must match the atmospheric
profile input in TAPE5

REPEAT TAPE4-RECORDS 2.1, 2.2 and 2.3 for each molecule : H2O, CO2, O3, C0 and NO


 ******  these records applicable only if IVIB eq 2 ***

TAPE4-RECORD 3.1 

 	CHRD(1)

              3

	 2x, A1

		CHRD(1):	a flag which indicates the beginning of input for
			        a new molecule; must be set to '-'


	The next two records are required for the following five molecules:
         H2O, CO2, O3, C0 and NO, in that order. All molecules must be input,
	 even if not used in NLTE calculations.
  
          
TAPE4-RECORD 3.2 

	HMNLTE

	    10

	   A10

		HMNLTE: 	molecule name

TAPE4-RECORD 3.3

	ALT,   (VPNE(I),I=1,NUM)

           (F7.0,1P,7E11.4,     /(18X, 6E11.4))

		ALT:	 altitude (km)

		VPNE(I): population for each mode I. Set to zero if the mode
			 is not desired. See Table IV for allowed modes and input order. 

REPEAT TAPE4-RECORD 3.3 for all altitudes; the altitude range must match the atmospheric
profile input in TAPE5

REPEAT TAPE4-RECORDS 3.1, 3.2 and 3.3 for each molecule : H2O, CO2, O3, C0 and NO

 _________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

Special LINUX note:

When running LINUX on the PGI compile in DOUBLE precision we encountered a "bug" with the 
compile.  Thus, one needs to run the script, src/linux_dbl_script, before using the makefile,
makefiles/makelbl.pgi_linux_f90_dbl.



 
